==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ophiophagus
<hw>O`phi*oph"a*gus</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>Ophiophagous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
venomous East Indian snakes, which feed on other snakes.
<spn>Ophiophagus elaps</spn> is said to be the largest and most deadly
of poisonous snakes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ophism</ent>⟦br⟧
